definitions.definition: Of a body in motion : the tendency of a body to maintain its inertial motion ; the product of its mass and velocity , or the vector sum of the products of its masses and velocities .
Strength or force gained by motion or movement.
The impetus , either of a body in motion, or of an idea or course of events ; a moment .
